      "narrativeName": "Vein Unleashed",
      "narrativeClass": "vein-experimental-notes",
      "narrative": "Under major breach conditions, <strong>VEIN-01</strong> exits vascular channels en masse, encasing and permeating Host-Prime in a mobile clot shell. Gross morphology remains “humanoid,” but internal anatomy becomes non-differentiable. Host reports retained executive function during events; telemetry suggests at least partial dissociation. <strong>VEIN-01</strong>'s end-state objective remains <strong class='strong-redacted'>[REDACTED]</strong>.",
      "entangledScar": "involuntaryStimulus",
