          "narrativeName": "Liquid Motion",
          "narrativeClass": "vein-experimental-notes",
          "narrative": "When uncontained, <strong>VEIN-01</strong> treats available architecture as a suspension lattice. Blood-mass extrudes along ceilings, beams, and walls, forming transient anchor points and tensile strands. Resultant locomotion displays near-frictionless redirection of momentum and markedly reduced acoustic profile (< 18 dB at 3 m).",
