          "narrativeClass": "vein-experimental-notes",
          "narrative": "Localized extensions of <strong>VEIN-01</strong> can be extruded into filamentous whips under high tension (see Fig. V-3). Initial contact typically presents as a superficial laceration; secondary systemic effects (complex V-<strong class='strong-redacted'>[REDACTED]</strong>) manifest after 1–3 minutes, including disorientation, hypotonia, and progressive loss of voluntary motor control.",
